cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a method for human pose estimation and tracking in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. The paper focuses on using temporal information between frames, which is a key aspect of video analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a network to learn both spatial and temporal information, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The proposed method also involves data augmentation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper uses the PoseTrack dataset, which is a dataset for human pose estimation and tracking in videos, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on tracking human poses in videos involves robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
